{"hash":"810fce27972948ee9a391861a2b5ef523a7099fb","data":{"page":{"title":"Blockchain &#038; Retail","content":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_cover_BIG-1024x576.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2742\" srcset=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_cover_BIG-1024x576.png 1024w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_cover_BIG-300x169.png 300w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_cover_BIG-768x432.png 768w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_cover_BIG-1536x864.png 1536w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_cover_BIG.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The retail industry has driven substantial change thanks to the growing demand of customers shifting to online shopping. This causes the need of creating&nbsp; systems and protocols which ensures complete safety and transparency through the steps of each process to reach the end user.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Benefits of Blockchain for Retail Industry:</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Customers’ demands are rapidly evolving and their expectations around delivery time, sourcing, transparency, and authenticity are changing, and blockchain is likely to play an important role in helping retailers deliver on those expectations, especially when it comes to mobile payments, supply chain, and finance applications.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Blockchain Use cases for Retail Industry:</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table style=\"border: none;\"><tbody><tr><td><img src=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_pictogram_1_SMALL.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"width: 128px;\"></td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"><strong>Product provenance &#8211; </strong>Blockchain technology has the ability to provide end-to-end transparency on the source and origin of ingredients and goods, boosting retailers’ reliability.</td></tr><tr><td><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_pictogram_2_SMAL.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"128\" height=\"128\"></td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"><strong>Fraud prevention &#8211; </strong>The ability to assign unique identifiers to each product is expected to provide unprecedented security in identifying counterfeit items in the supply chain, as well as catching and rejecting fraudulent returns on time.</td></tr><tr><td><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_pictogram_3_SMALL.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"128\" height=\"128\"></td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"><strong>Accepting payments with cryptocurrencies &#8211; </strong>Blockchain enables retailers to accept cryptocurrency payments, which is advantageous for cross-border payments and micropayments. The use of smart contracts contributes to instant payments, automated refunds, and much more.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_infographic_BIG-1024x576.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2743\" srcset=\"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_infographic_BIG-1024x576.png 1024w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_infographic_BIG-300x169.png 300w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_infographic_BIG-768x432.png 768w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_infographic_BIG-1536x864.png 1536w, https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_infographic_BIG.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n","id":"2705","parent":2557,"excerpt":"<p>The major problems  that blockchain tackles within the Retail Sector such as product fraud, food safety, high transaction costs, and customer’s shifting loyalty are attractive enough to involve every business in this industry. The prize is large and multi-faceted: improved transparency, reduced fraud, greater safety, heightened efficiency and, above all, enhanced customer trust.<br />\nBlockchain is a system that encourages more authentic interactions between customers and companies, promoting loyalty through transparency. Blockchain integrates with current systems to facilitate real time data, enabling better understanding of customers needs and faster transactions.</p>\n","link":"https://hack.bg/how-blockchain-works/blockchain-retail/","modified":"2021-03-29T14:15:46","featuredMedia":{"sourceUrl":"https://hack.bg/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Case-study_Retail_cover_BIG.png","altText":"","mimeType":"image/png","mediaDetails":{"width":1920,"height":1080}},"tags":[]}},"context":{}}